10:28.461 --> 10:30.255
‐ Ethan, across The Forge

10:30.255 --> 10:32.257
with the oxyacetylene torch.
‐ Ah...

10:32.257 --> 10:33.758
‐ Little edge quench.

10:33.758 --> 10:35.385
<i>‐ I'm doing an edge quench,</i>

10:35.385 --> 10:37.595
<i>because I wanna leave</i>
<i>that back soft</i>

10:37.595 --> 10:39.264
<i>and the cutting edge hard,</i>

10:39.264 --> 10:41.850
<i>so that it will give the blade</i>
<i>more strength,</i>

10:41.850 --> 10:45.019
and, ideally,
prevent it from breaking.

10:45.019 --> 10:47.730
‐ Ethan is taking quite a while
to get up to heat.

10:47.730 --> 10:49.190
<i>‐ It's taking me a while,</i>

10:49.190 --> 10:50.608
<i>because the blade's</i>
<i>still thicker</i>

10:50.608 --> 10:52.277
<i>than I would normally get it,</i>

10:52.277 --> 10:54.279
and a lot thicker
than I would like.

10:54.279 --> 10:57.282
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:57.282 --> 11:00.326
<i>[cymbal shimmering]</i>

11:00.326 --> 11:03.288
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:03.288 --> 11:04.789
<i>‐ I'm using the grinder</i>

11:04.789 --> 11:07.292
<i>to get as much of</i>
<i>the surface material off</i>

11:07.292 --> 11:09.002
<i>to thin out the blade,</i>

11:09.002 --> 11:11.296
and perhaps even put
a little bevel in there,

11:11.296 --> 11:13.298
<i>so that I can get it ready</i>
<i>for the quench</i>

11:13.298 --> 11:15.466
<i>in this last few moments.</i>

11:15.466 --> 11:17.010
‐ What is Steve doing?

11:17.010 --> 11:19.888
‐ He's gonna grind himself
a knife.

11:19.888 --> 11:23.474
‐ Amy and Steve are having
a grinder war,

11:23.474 --> 11:25.727
so that they can quench
and harden their blades.

11:25.727 --> 11:28.146
‐ Ah. This is making me nuts.

11:28.146 --> 11:31.024
Quench these blades,
then put them in a vise,

11:31.024 --> 11:32.483
and then grind on them.

11:32.483 --> 11:35.778
‐ With ten minutes left,
nobody is done.

11:35.778 --> 11:38.740
It's gonna be very interesting
to see what happens here.

11:38.740 --> 11:40.241
<i>‐ I'm feeling nervous.</i>

11:40.241 --> 11:42.619
‐ I need to make this thing
look like a knife.

11:42.619 --> 11:44.579
<i>‐ I'm not gonna be turning in</i>
<i>at all</i>

11:44.579 --> 11:49.292
<i>the blade that I wanted.</i>

11:49.292 --> 11:51.252
‐ With ten minutes left,
nobody is done,

11:51.252 --> 11:53.129
nobody is perfect.

11:53.129 --> 11:55.965
It's gonna be very interesting
to see what happens here.

11:55.965 --> 11:58.343
<i>‐ It's not gonna be pretty,</i>
<i>it's not gonna be shiny,</i>

11:58.343 --> 12:00.011
but it sure is gonna be done.

12:00.011 --> 12:01.846
‐ Come on,
quench that dang blade.

12:01.846 --> 12:05.683
<i>[tense music]</i>

12:05.683 --> 12:07.936
‐ If this blade isn't hardened,

12:07.936 --> 12:09.229
I'm out.

12:09.229 --> 12:11.564
<i>♪</i> ♪

12:11.564 --> 12:13.316
All right.

12:13.316 --> 12:16.194
<i>I think my blade</i>
<i>is pretty straight...</i>

12:16.194 --> 12:17.362
and I think it's hard.

12:17.362 --> 12:19.697
‐ Five, four...

12:19.697 --> 12:22.200
three, two, one.

12:22.200 --> 12:24.452
Bladesmiths, drop your tools,
shut down your machines.

12:24.452 --> 12:27.747
This round of competition
is over.

12:27.747 --> 12:31.209
<i>‐ I don't think my blade is</i>
<i>up to the judges' standards.</i>

12:31.209 --> 12:33.336
I know I don't believe
it's up to mine.

12:33.336 --> 12:36.547
<i>I'm probably gonna be</i>
<i>the one sent home.</i>

12:36.547 --> 12:38.216
<i>[solemn music]</i>

12:38.216 --> 12:39.634
‐ All right, bladesmiths,

12:39.634 --> 12:42.220
our first round of
pinball mania is over.

12:42.220 --> 12:43.596
Now it's time for the judges

12:43.596 --> 12:45.265
to take a closer look
at your work.

12:45.265 --> 12:46.849
Steve, you're up first.

12:46.849 --> 12:49.644
Please present your blade
to the judges.

12:49.644 --> 12:51.396
<i>♪</i> ♪

12:51.396 --> 12:53.731
<i>‐ Well, Steve, the weight of</i>
<i>what you got here is good.</i>

12:53.731 --> 12:55.733
Some of the problems
you had with the forge weld

12:55.733 --> 12:57.277
was that you weren't
cleaning the steel,

12:57.277 --> 13:00.697
and there's some delaminations
or cold shuts

13:00.697 --> 13:02.865
that go all the way
along the spine.

13:02.865 --> 13:04.867
<i>There's a pretty big one</i>
<i>here at the end.</i>

13:04.867 --> 13:06.452
I mean,
if you move forward from here,

13:06.452 --> 13:08.288
I'd be interested to see
how you can clean this up

13:08.288 --> 13:10.540
and get along with it.

13:10.540 --> 13:12.292
‐ Ethan, you're up next.

13:12.292 --> 13:13.835
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:13.835 --> 13:15.378
<i>‐ This is</i>
<i>a good‐looking knife.</i>

13:15.378 --> 13:18.006
I can see the forge weld
moving across here,

13:18.006 --> 13:20.842
but I can't get a finger in it,
which is a good thing.

13:20.842 --> 13:23.261
I mean, altogether,
I think it's well on its way.

13:23.261 --> 13:25.888
Nicely done.
‐ [exhales]

13:25.888 --> 13:28.725
‐ Michael, you're next.

13:28.725 --> 13:29.851
<i>‐ All right, Michael,</i>

13:29.851 --> 13:32.186
first up, nice clean lines.

13:32.186 --> 13:33.604
<i>You do have a blemish here.</i>

13:33.604 --> 13:35.315
<i>That's the main concern</i>
<i>of this.</i>

13:35.315 --> 13:37.275
But it's not on the edge,

13:37.275 --> 13:38.651
it's not on the spine.

13:38.651 --> 13:40.320
The question is,
do you go for looks

13:40.320 --> 13:42.238
or do you go
for structural integrity

13:42.238 --> 13:44.574
when you're fixing that?

13:44.574 --> 13:46.576
‐ Amy, you're up.

13:46.576 --> 13:49.120
<i>‐ This knife is</i>
<i>completely solid.</i>

13:49.120 --> 13:51.122
I don't see
any forge weld problems.

13:51.122 --> 13:52.415
Well done.

13:52.415 --> 13:54.292
‐ Watching you set this up
was great,

13:54.292 --> 13:56.127
and then when you started
to draw this out, I thought,

13:56.127 --> 13:58.796
"There's no way
you've got enough material

13:58.796 --> 14:01.007
to get it drawn out
into this length."

14:01.007 --> 14:02.925
I just‐‐it looked small to me.

14:02.925 --> 14:07.764
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:07.764 --> 14:09.974
Okay, so, parameters were...

14:09.974 --> 14:12.602
‐ 11 to 13 inches, Dave.

14:12.602 --> 14:14.729
‐ Okay...

14:14.729 --> 14:17.857
I've got a blade
that's 10 and 3/8.

14:17.857 --> 14:19.734
<i>[tense tone]</i>

14:19.734 --> 14:22.028
‐ You were told, before we
ever started the first round,

14:22.028 --> 14:24.405
that failure to meet even
a single one of our parameters

14:24.405 --> 14:27.033
was grounds for immediate
dismissal from The Forge.

14:27.033 --> 14:30.036
Amy, if you can't
make parameters,

14:30.036 --> 14:32.497
then you can't be
the "Forged in Fire" champion,

14:32.497 --> 14:33.831
and for that reason,

14:33.831 --> 14:36.834
I have to ask you
to please leave The Forge.

14:36.834 --> 14:39.128
<i>‐ I know I made</i>
<i>a solid piece of steel,</i>

14:39.128 --> 14:42.256
but as those last two minutes
ticked down,

14:42.256 --> 14:44.258
<i>I forgot to measure.</i>

14:44.258 --> 14:46.177
To future contestants,
I would say,

14:46.177 --> 14:48.846
<i>don't get bogged down</i>
<i>in perfection.</i>

14:48.846 --> 14:52.225
Be decisive, be careful,
but be quick.

14:52.225 --> 14:55.061
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:55.061 --> 14:57.188
<i>[dynamic orchestral music]</i>

14:57.188 --> 14:59.023
‐ Bladesmiths, congratulations.

14:59.023 --> 15:01.150
You've made it to the second
round of this competition.

15:01.150 --> 15:03.277
Now that those blades
have been tempered,

15:03.277 --> 15:05.113
it's time to turn them into
fully functional weapons

15:05.113 --> 15:07.240
by attaching handles to them

15:07.240 --> 15:09.450
so that we can test them
for strength and durability

15:09.450 --> 15:12.036
<i>in a pinball plunger smash,</i>

15:12.036 --> 15:15.081
and for edge retention
in a loot bag slice.

15:15.081 --> 15:18.417
Some of you have more work
to do than others,

15:18.417 --> 15:20.211
but use your time wisely,

15:20.211 --> 15:22.880
because you have
only three hours in this round.

15:22.880 --> 15:24.090
Good luck.

15:24.090 --> 15:26.717
Your three hours starts...

15:26.717 --> 15:28.136
now.

15:28.136 --> 15:29.887
<i>[rock music]</i>

15:29.887 --> 15:32.265
<i>‐ I am excited</i>
<i>to be in round two,</i>

15:32.265 --> 15:35.059
but I am definitely
the underdog.

15:35.059 --> 15:36.727
<i>I have a lot of delaminations.</i>

15:36.727 --> 15:38.229
I'm seeing if I can
even things out

15:38.229 --> 15:39.814
and get it ready for a handle.

15:39.814 --> 15:42.191
‐ Steve's blade
is relatively thin,

15:42.191 --> 15:44.485
so he really can't afford
to take that much meat

15:44.485 --> 15:46.237
out of that blade, right?

15:46.237 --> 15:47.822
‐ He's gotta do
some creative grinding.

15:47.822 --> 15:49.407
‐ Yeah.

15:49.407 --> 15:50.950
‐ I have to keep checking it
to make sure

15:50.950 --> 15:55.288
it's not thinning out
the blade too much.

15:55.288 --> 15:57.081
‐ Over here,
we have Michael's blade.

15:57.081 --> 15:58.249
Very thin.

15:58.249 --> 16:00.251
These things have to
be able to withstand

16:00.251 --> 16:02.336
a pinball plunger smash.

16:02.336 --> 16:05.089
<i>‐ My strategy is</i>
<i>to address that cold shut.</i>

16:05.089 --> 16:07.300
It's big, it's deep,
and it's pretty glaring.

16:07.300 --> 16:10.303
‐ Michael continuing to thin
the sides of his blade.

16:10.303 --> 16:12.972
‐ My concern is,
where's that delamination go?

16:12.972 --> 16:15.349
And as he grinds
thinner and thinner,

16:15.349 --> 16:17.059
is he going to open that up?

16:17.059 --> 16:18.811
<i>‐ Doing the grinding</i>
<i>appropriately,</i>

16:18.811 --> 16:22.023
so I don't screw myself over,
is kinda hard.

16:22.023 --> 16:24.442
‐ That one pockmark there
is not going away,

16:24.442 --> 16:26.611
so at this point,
leave it alone.

16:26.611 --> 16:28.863
<i>‐ By the thickness</i>
<i>that I have left,</i>

16:28.863 --> 16:31.490
I can't afford to take off
anymore material,

16:31.490 --> 16:33.034
<i>so I'm calling it good.</i>

16:33.034 --> 16:35.077
Ha‐ha. Noice.

16:35.077 --> 16:36.579
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:36.579 --> 16:38.122
<i>‐ I think I'll be able to fix</i>

16:38.122 --> 16:40.416
most of the issues
that I have with my blade,

16:40.416 --> 16:42.460
but my first priority's
gonna be a handle,

16:42.460 --> 16:44.378
because if it doesn't
have a handle,

16:44.378 --> 16:46.422
<i>they're not gonna be</i>
<i>able to test it at all.</i>

16:46.422 --> 16:49.300
The materials I decided to use
for my handle construction

16:49.300 --> 16:51.427
<i>is a piece of brass</i>
<i>for the guard,</i>

16:51.427 --> 16:53.512
<i>and a piece of</i>
<i>white oak wood.</i>

16:53.512 --> 16:55.056
Looks like white oak.

16:55.056 --> 16:56.891
The guard was not a parameter,
but in my opinion,

16:56.891 --> 16:59.769
<i>the best way to protect</i>
<i>the person using it,</i>

16:59.769 --> 17:02.146
it needed a guard.
[drill whirring]

17:02.146 --> 17:04.232
‐ You know,
it's nice to see a smith

17:04.232 --> 17:08.194
doing such meticulous
and tightfitting work.

17:08.194 --> 17:09.320
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:09.320 --> 17:10.821
<i>‐ With my grinding done,</i>

17:10.821 --> 17:12.698
<i>it's time to move on</i>
<i>to my handle,</i>

17:12.698 --> 17:16.118
which means I need
to get holes into my tang.

17:16.118 --> 17:17.828
<i>I drill holes in my tang,</i>

17:17.828 --> 17:20.790
but the fit is not ideal...

17:20.790 --> 17:22.416
[bleep].

17:22.416 --> 17:24.168
<i>So I have to drill</i>
<i>a little bit more</i>

17:24.168 --> 17:26.629
to make them less of an issue.

17:26.629 --> 17:29.924
This is almost exactly
what I was anticipating:

17:29.924 --> 17:31.259
<i>not enough time,</i>

17:31.259 --> 17:33.469
little problems
throughout the process

17:33.469 --> 17:35.513
<i>that just throw me off.</i>

17:35.513 --> 17:37.557
‐ When we talk about
a timed competition,

17:37.557 --> 17:39.392
those little seconds,
they turn into minutes,

17:39.392 --> 17:41.435
and then minutes
turns into an hour gone,

17:41.435 --> 17:44.772
and that's 1/3 of your time.

17:44.772 --> 17:48.442
‐ So, Steve has drilled
four holes in his tank,

17:48.442 --> 17:51.571
and then freehand drilled them
through the wood.

17:51.571 --> 17:54.699
The odds of all holes
lining up perfectly

17:54.699 --> 17:56.450
are very small.

17:56.450 --> 17:59.704
<i>‐ I've chosen Corby bolts</i>
<i>that have two pieces to them,</i>

17:59.704 --> 18:02.164
<i>and I'm going to put them</i>
<i>through the holes,</i>

18:02.164 --> 18:05.084
and get them to connect
in the center.

18:05.084 --> 18:06.377
[bleep].

18:06.377 --> 18:07.628
<i>I start assembling everything</i>

18:07.628 --> 18:09.213
<i>with the Corby bolts,</i>

18:09.213 --> 18:12.508
and I'm running into
a little issue with lining up.

18:12.508 --> 18:14.844
‐ What Steve's fighting with
are these Corbys.

18:14.844 --> 18:17.096
You've got holes lined up,

18:17.096 --> 18:19.098
but maybe one of them's
a little bit off,

18:19.098 --> 18:21.726
so that blade never falls
into the barrel.

18:21.726 --> 18:23.227
<i>‐ If I can't get this</i>
<i>together,</i>

18:23.227 --> 18:24.937
<i>then I'm gonna</i>
<i>have to start over.</i>

18:24.937 --> 18:27.565
I just don't have time
to make a new handle.

18:27.565 --> 18:30.359
I've gotta move,
so I'm gonna have four holes

18:30.359 --> 18:31.944
with three Corby bolts.

18:31.944 --> 18:34.864
<i>Having three of</i>
<i>these Corby bolts in there</i>

18:34.864 --> 18:36.115
is not gonna look right,

18:36.115 --> 18:39.619
<i>but it'll still hold together.</i>

18:39.619 --> 18:40.745
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:40.745 --> 18:42.913
‐ I've got my handle fitted up,

18:42.913 --> 18:44.540
<i>so I start fixing</i>

18:44.540 --> 18:47.084
what the judges
recommended me to fix.

18:47.084 --> 18:50.546
I have a slight delamination,
but it's in a really good spot,

18:50.546 --> 18:52.256
because I can cover it up
with a false edge.

18:52.256 --> 18:53.758
‐ Interesting.

18:53.758 --> 18:56.552
Ethan had a delamination
on the tip of his spine.

18:56.552 --> 18:58.429
Basically a false edge
right now.

18:58.429 --> 19:00.306
‐ Yeah.
‐ Which is a little bit tricky

19:00.306 --> 19:02.099
in a timed competition
like this,

19:02.099 --> 19:04.435
to get both angles of
the false edge correct.

19:04.435 --> 19:06.103
<i>‐ The false edge</i>
<i>doesn't completely</i>

19:06.103 --> 19:08.105
get rid of the delamination,

19:08.105 --> 19:10.483
but it does get
the worst of it out.

19:10.483 --> 19:13.653
‐ You have 45 minutes
remaining in this round!

19:13.653 --> 19:15.905
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:15.905 --> 19:17.406
<i>‐ For the sharpness test,</i>

19:17.406 --> 19:19.450
I'm gonna put
a wicked edge on there,

19:19.450 --> 19:20.826
but it can't be too thin,

19:20.826 --> 19:23.287
<i>because for the pinball</i>
<i>plunger smash,</i>

19:23.287 --> 19:24.914
<i>it has to be strong enough.</i>

19:24.914 --> 19:26.874
<i>I don't want my edge</i>
<i>to roll over or chip.</i>

19:26.874 --> 19:28.459
‐ Doesn't that finishing belt

19:28.459 --> 19:30.419
take off small bits of steel
as you...

19:30.419 --> 19:32.004
‐ It does.

19:32.004 --> 19:33.964
<i>‐ As soon as I finish</i>
<i>sharpening on the grinder,</i>

19:33.964 --> 19:36.884
I get a wet stone
and a piece of leather

19:36.884 --> 19:38.302
<i>that I can strop with,</i>

19:38.302 --> 19:41.305
<i>just making sure</i>
<i>that edge is polished</i>

19:41.305 --> 19:42.682
and really sharp.

19:42.682 --> 19:44.892
<i>My blade is very sharp.</i>

19:44.892 --> 19:48.896
There is very little hair
on my forearm now.

19:48.896 --> 19:52.650
"This blade, it will shave."

19:52.650 --> 19:54.777
<i>‐ The clock is ticking down,</i>

19:54.777 --> 19:57.196
<i>so I start</i>
<i>profiling my handle.</i>

19:57.196 --> 20:00.408
I'm going for
a fighter style shape.

20:00.408 --> 20:02.326
‐ He's gonna take
that 1‐inch contact oil

20:02.326 --> 20:04.328
and contour the handle
and the guard

20:04.328 --> 20:06.831
all in one shot,
and make it seamless.

20:06.831 --> 20:09.750
‐ I intend to have a palm swell
and a thinner spot

20:09.750 --> 20:12.002
down where your pinky
and ring finger would be,

20:12.002 --> 20:15.047
so that your hand would fit
really nicely to the handle.

20:15.047 --> 20:16.507
‐ Ooh.

20:16.507 --> 20:18.509
I kinda like what Ethan did
to the back of that handle.

20:18.509 --> 20:20.136
‐ It's really nice work.

20:20.136 --> 20:21.721
<i>‐ I am finishing up the handle</i>

20:21.721 --> 20:24.265
<i>to make it to where</i>
<i>it would fit in my hand.</i>

20:24.265 --> 20:26.350
I don't know if it'll work
for the judges' hands,

20:26.350 --> 20:28.185
but I can't use their hands,

20:28.185 --> 20:30.354
so it's all I got.

20:30.354 --> 20:32.148
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:32.148 --> 20:34.358
‐ Ten minutes, bladesmiths.

20:34.358 --> 20:36.527
<i>‐ I need to get</i>
<i>my final edge on.</i>

20:36.527 --> 20:38.696
I have gotta get
this thing done.

20:38.696 --> 20:41.365
‐ Yeah, see, grinding as hard
as he's grinding right there‐‐

20:41.365 --> 20:43.451
[snaps, rattles]
‐ Oh!

20:43.451 --> 20:45.202
‐ That's why
you don't use those.

20:45.202 --> 20:46.579
‐ Yep.

20:46.579 --> 20:48.873
‐ There goes a belt.
[bleep].

20:48.873 --> 20:50.708
I'm already down to the wire...

20:50.708 --> 20:52.668
‐ Five minutes, bladesmiths.

20:52.668 --> 20:55.880
‐ So this is extremely
frustrating for me.

20:55.880 --> 20:58.090
‐ Those belts are
finishing belts,

20:58.090 --> 21:00.092
so pushing really hard on them,

21:00.092 --> 21:02.011
you hear that tang going
"wack, wack, wack, wack, wack,"

21:02.011 --> 21:03.554
'cause it's shattering.

21:03.554 --> 21:05.848
Let the tool do the work.
<i>‐ I'm feeling anxious.</i>

21:05.848 --> 21:07.600
<i>I know I'm gonna get it done,</i>

21:07.600 --> 21:10.436
but it may not be
quite good enough.

21:10.436 --> 21:12.396
‐ Five, four...

21:12.396 --> 21:15.649
three, two, one.

21:15.649 --> 21:18.027
Bladesmiths, shut down
your machines, drop your tools.

21:18.027 --> 21:20.905
This round of competition
is over.

21:20.905 --> 21:22.406
‐ Whew!

21:22.406 --> 21:24.617
<i>My blade is sleek, it's thin.</i>

21:24.617 --> 21:27.203
<i>I'm just crossing my fingers</i>
<i>that my knife doesn't break</i>

21:27.203 --> 21:30.247
and that it performs well
in their tests.

21:33.042 --> 21:34.460
<i>[metallic clang]‐ Hell.</i>

21:34.460 --> 21:35.628
Welcome to the strength test.

21:35.628 --> 21:37.922
Now, in the firs

21:37.922 --> 21:40.925
from a poor, defenseless
pinball machine.

21:40.925 --> 21:43.093
Well, here's its big brother,

21:43.093 --> 21:46.555
and he's here for revenge.
<i>[man cackling]</i>

21:46.555 --> 21:48.432
To test the strength
and durability of your edge,

21:48.432 --> 21:50.434
as well as the overall
construction of your blade,

21:50.434 --> 21:53.187
I'll be launching
that 5200 nine‐pound pinball

21:53.187 --> 21:55.439
at the edge of your knives
three times.

21:55.439 --> 21:57.149
Steve, you're up first.
You ready?

21:57.149 --> 21:58.943
‐ I'm ready.

21:58.943 --> 22:00.444
<i>I'm nervous.</i>

22:00.444 --> 22:03.030
When Ben launches
this pinball at my blade,

22:03.030 --> 22:04.907
I don't wanna see it break.

22:04.907 --> 22:07.952
<i>[tense music]</i>

22:07.952 --> 22:10.162
<i>♪</i> ♪

22:10.162 --> 22:13.207
<i>[rock music]</i>

22:13.207 --> 22:20.005
<i>♪</i> ♪

22:27.304 --> 22:28.597
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:28.597 --> 22:30.599
‐ Well, Steve,
I like the shape of your blade,

22:30.599 --> 22:32.560
I like the fold and bend to it,

22:32.560 --> 22:35.354
but, uh,
the pinball did some damage.

22:35.354 --> 22:37.940
There's some rolls
up here at the edge.

22:37.940 --> 22:41.402
There's also some gapping here
at the handle in the back

22:41.402 --> 22:43.445
and in the front.

22:43.445 --> 22:44.989
But it all held up.

22:44.989 --> 22:46.824
Well done.
‐ Thank you.

22:46.824 --> 22:48.325
‐ All right, Ethan,
you're up next.

22:48.325 --> 22:49.785
Are you ready?

22:49.785 --> 22:51.620
‐ I suppose.
‐ You suppose. [chuckles]

22:51.620 --> 22:53.372
Well, I suppose
I'm gonna do it.

22:53.372 --> 22:55.332
‐ [chuckles]

22:55.332 --> 22:57.084
<i>I'm really starting to wonder,</i>

22:57.084 --> 22:59.461
<i>is my blade gonna hold up</i>
<i>to this?</i>

22:59.461 --> 23:02.172
This is the size of the thing
they're shooting at my blade.

23:02.172 --> 23:03.924
<i>[cymbal shimmering]</i>

23:03.924 --> 23:06.927
<i>[rock music]</i>

23:06.927 --> 23:13.976
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:25.195 --> 23:27.489
‐ Well, Ethan,
first things first,

23:27.489 --> 23:28.908
it did take some rolling.

23:28.908 --> 23:31.493
The handle is a little bit big.

23:31.493 --> 23:34.038
There's a lot of handle
left over on this knife.

23:34.038 --> 23:36.040
But I love how you relieved
all the, uh‐‐

23:36.040 --> 23:38.083
all the grinds
on your guard here.

23:38.083 --> 23:40.127
Beautiful knife.
‐ Thank you.

23:40.127 --> 23:42.004
‐ Michael, you're up.
Are you ready?

23:42.004 --> 23:43.213
‐ I am.

23:43.213 --> 23:49.845
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:04.443 --> 24:05.986
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

24:05.986 --> 24:08.656
‐ Well, Michael, being that
your blade is so thin,

24:08.656 --> 24:11.784
you have the most flexible of
the blades that are out there.

24:11.784 --> 24:13.827
It ended up,
that flexibility gave you

24:13.827 --> 24:15.287
a little advantage
in this test,

24:15.287 --> 24:17.581
'cause the edge rolling
that's here,

24:17.581 --> 24:19.833
and there is some,
it's not bad.

24:19.833 --> 24:22.753
Well done.
‐ Thank you.

24:22.753 --> 24:24.254
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:24.254 --> 24:27.883
‐ Bladesmiths,
this is the loot bag slice.

24:27.883 --> 24:30.469
To test the edge of your blade,
I will take your weapon,

24:30.469 --> 24:32.596
and I will slash
all these loot bags empty

24:32.596 --> 24:34.932
and liberating
the prizes in there.

24:34.932 --> 24:36.767
Now, unlike the strength test,

24:36.767 --> 24:38.560
this is all about
what the edge of your blade

24:38.560 --> 24:40.437
will do to these loot bags.

24:40.437 --> 24:42.106
Steve, you're up first.
You ready?

24:42.106 --> 24:43.774
‐ I'm ready.

24:43.774 --> 24:46.318
<i>With the damage my blade took</i>
<i>from the pinball,</i>

24:46.318 --> 24:50.030
I'm a little concerned
about this loot bag slice.

24:50.030 --> 24:55.452
<i>[music intensifies]</i>

24:55.452 --> 25:02.501
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:06.630 --> 25:08.799
<i>[solemn music]</i>

25:08.799 --> 25:12.177
‐ All right, Steve, as you can
see, in slicing this bag,

25:12.177 --> 25:14.430
it just cuts
on the impact area.

25:14.430 --> 25:16.140
On the slice itself,

25:16.140 --> 25:18.642
it didn't cut the bag open.

25:18.642 --> 25:21.645
Steve, sadly your blade, sir,

25:21.645 --> 25:23.230
did not really cut.

25:23.230 --> 25:25.315
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:25.315 --> 25:27.401
Ethan, your turn. You ready?

25:27.401 --> 25:28.902
‐ I suppose.

25:28.902 --> 25:31.113
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:31.113 --> 25:34.575
<i>[music intensifies]</i>

25:34.575 --> 25:37.578
<i>[rock music]</i>

25:37.578 --> 25:43.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:43.083 --> 25:44.752
[coins rattling]

25:45.753 --> 25:47.379
<i>[cymbal shimmering]</i>

25:47.379 --> 25:49.840
‐ All right, Ethan, let's talk
about your handle here.

25:49.840 --> 25:52.593
The swell you have there
makes my hand go

25:52.593 --> 25:54.636
only in one spot
where it's comfortable,

25:54.636 --> 25:56.638
but because you have
such a large handle,

25:56.638 --> 25:58.932
if you go to other spots,
it gets in the way.

25:58.932 --> 26:00.350
Now, your edge:

26:00.350 --> 26:03.103
As you can see,
it cuts in every movement.

26:03.103 --> 26:06.523
It liberated the contents,
which allows me to say,

26:06.523 --> 26:08.859
your blade, sir, will cut.

26:08.859 --> 26:10.360
Good job.
‐ Thank you.

26:10.360 --> 26:11.737
‐ All right, Michael,
your turn, you ready?

26:11.737 --> 26:13.489
‐ Oh, yeah.

26:13.489 --> 26:16.033
Steve's knife struggled
with the loot bag slice;

26:16.033 --> 26:18.202
<i>Ethan's obliterated the bag.</i>

26:18.202 --> 26:21.121
<i>I'm feeling</i>
<i>a little bit nervous.</i>

26:21.121 --> 26:28.128
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:34.093 --> 26:35.511
<i>[cymbal shimmering]</i>

26:35.511 --> 26:36.970
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:36.970 --> 26:38.806
‐ First up,
your edge is sharp enough

26:38.806 --> 26:40.766
to cut this loot bag open.

26:40.766 --> 26:42.476
It feels good in the hand.

26:42.476 --> 26:43.894
It was easy to move around
with your blade.

26:43.894 --> 26:46.897
And overall, sir,
your blade will cut.

26:46.897 --> 26:49.566
<i>[percussive music]</i>

26:49.566 --> 26:52.569
‐ Bladesmiths, the judges'
deliberation is complete.

26:52.569 --> 26:54.571
It's time for one of you
to leave The Forge.

26:54.571 --> 26:57.533
The bladesmith leaving
The Forge is...

26:57.533 --> 26:59.910
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

26:59.910 --> 27:03.080
Steve.
Your blade didn't make the cut.

27:03.080 --> 27:05.999
‐ Steve, all of the blades took
the same kinda amount of damage

27:05.999 --> 27:07.668
during the strength test,

27:07.668 --> 27:10.254
<i>but the sharpness test,</i>
<i>your blade just didn't cut,</i>

27:10.254 --> 27:12.631
and for that reason,
we're sending you home.

27:12.631 --> 27:15.175
‐ Steve, please surrender
your blade.

27:15.175 --> 27:16.593
<i>[rock music]</i>

27:16.593 --> 27:18.762
<i>‐ This is a really great</i>
<i>experience.</i>

27:18.762 --> 27:22.015
<i>I was able to not only see</i>
<i>other smiths at work,</i>

27:22.015 --> 27:24.768
but also to push my own limits.

27:24.768 --> 27:26.478
<i>I have learned</i>
<i>some things here,</i>

27:26.478 --> 27:28.814
<i>and I'm going to take them</i>
<i>to my own shop,</i>

27:28.814 --> 27:32.150
and I may just make
another six‐hour knife.

27:32.150 --> 27:37.447
<i>♪</i> ♪

27:37.447 --> 27:39.199
‐ Michael, Ethan,
congratulations.

27:39.199 --> 27:41.785
You've made it into the final
round of this competition.

27:41.785 --> 27:43.620
Now we're sending you
back to your home forges

27:43.620 --> 27:46.874
to recreate an iconic weapon
from history.

27:46.874 --> 27:48.750
That weapon is...

27:48.750 --> 27:52.296
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

27:52.296 --> 27:53.881
A barbarian sword.

27:53.881 --> 27:57.009
‐ Oh...
‐ Yeah.

27:57.009 --> 27:58.927
<i>‐ Weapons like this sword</i>

27:58.927 --> 28:01.430
<i>pay homage to classic</i>
<i>barbarian fantasy films</i>

28:01.430 --> 28:03.974
<i>and the uncivilized</i>
<i>and savage voyeurs of history</i>

28:03.974 --> 28:05.601
<i>who inspired them.</i>

28:05.601 --> 28:08.020
<i>The long, stout sword</i>
<i>is simple in design,</i>

28:08.020 --> 28:10.606
<i>but it's a violent hacking</i>
<i>and slashing weapon,</i>

28:10.606 --> 28:12.983
<i>due to its light weight</i>
<i>and sharp double‐edge.</i>

28:12.983 --> 28:15.193
<i>Perhaps most famously featured</i>
<i>in the film</i>

28:15.193 --> 28:16.737
<i>"Conan the Barbarian,"</i>

28:16.737 --> 28:19.072
<i>this sword is ideally suited</i>
<i>to the ruthless</i>

28:19.072 --> 28:20.490
<i>and frenzied fighting style</i>

28:20.490 --> 28:23.827
<i>brought to life</i>
<i>in these films.</i>

28:23.827 --> 28:26.246
Your blades must fall within
the following parameters:

28:26.246 --> 28:28.498
It must be sharpened
on both edges

28:28.498 --> 28:30.500
and have a fuller
on both sides.

28:30.500 --> 28:32.502
You must have a handle
that's leather‐wrapped,

28:32.502 --> 28:34.755
and you must also
include a pommel.

28:34.755 --> 28:38.842
‐ This weapon has to be
rugged, brutal, sharp.

28:38.842 --> 28:40.510
<i>It's made to destroy.</i>

28:40.510 --> 28:43.347
This is gonna be
a fun adventure.

28:43.347 --> 28:45.432
‐ You'll have five days
at your home forges

28:45.432 --> 28:47.392
in which to complete
this challenge.

28:47.392 --> 28:49.102
At the end of five days,

28:49.102 --> 28:51.521
you'll return and present
your badass steel

28:51.521 --> 28:53.982
to our panel of barbarians.
‐ [chuckles]

28:53.982 --> 28:58.570
‐ And only after they've gone
mad mayhem with those things

28:58.570 --> 29:00.864
will they declare one of you
worthy of the title

29:00.864 --> 29:04.660
"Forged in Fire" champion
and that check for $10,000.

29:04.660 --> 29:06.787
Good luck, bladesmiths.
We'll see you in five days.

29:09.122 --> 29:11.375
<i>[rock music]</i>

29:11.375 --> 29:13.877
<i>‐ This is day one</i>
<i>at my home forge.</i>

29:13.877 --> 29:15.253
My plan for the first day

29:15.253 --> 29:17.881
is to get the blade
rough‐forged out.

29:17.881 --> 29:20.342
<i>I also wanna get</i>
<i>the Damascus pieces made</i>

29:20.342 --> 29:22.552
<i>for the handle.</i>

29:22.552 --> 29:25.138
So, I'm gonna weld up
my canister.

29:25.138 --> 29:27.140
I currently am in the Navy.

29:27.140 --> 29:29.851
<i>I wanna make the pommel</i>
<i>out of submarine hole shavings</i>

29:29.851 --> 29:31.937
mixed with powdered steel,
because I think it'll be

29:31.937 --> 29:34.564
a very unique touch
to my barbarian sword.

29:34.564 --> 29:37.025
Probably wanna let this
canister soak in the forge

29:37.025 --> 29:39.569
long enough to make sure
it gets welded.

29:39.569 --> 29:41.947
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:41.947 --> 29:44.408
Solid as it can be to me.

29:44.408 --> 29:47.995
The key to get this barbarian
sword correct is,

29:47.995 --> 29:50.414
<i>I need to make sure</i>
<i>it's lightweight enough,</i>

29:50.414 --> 29:52.082
but yet thick enough

29:52.082 --> 29:55.210
that the blade can
take a beating.

29:55.210 --> 29:57.754
All right, that's a day.

29:57.754 --> 29:59.798
<i>[country rock music]</i>

29:59.798 --> 30:02.009
[metal clanking]

30:02.009 --> 30:03.510
<i>‐ I started out</i>
<i>forging this blade</i>

30:03.510 --> 30:05.595
out of this chunk of 5160.

30:05.595 --> 30:08.890
I have a lot of drawing to do
by hand.

30:08.890 --> 30:10.600
This is gonna suck.

30:10.600 --> 30:13.437
It's just not moving
the way I want it to.

30:13.437 --> 30:17.274
<i>With the 5160, you only have</i>
<i>a short window of time</i>

30:17.274 --> 30:19.943
before it cools down too much
and gets too hard to move.

30:19.943 --> 30:23.155
<i>I just don't have the stamina</i>
<i>to continue forging on</i>

30:23.155 --> 30:24.448
with this type of steel.

30:24.448 --> 30:26.033
I'm gonna‐‐[chuckles]‐‐

30:26.033 --> 30:28.118
change plans a little.

30:28.118 --> 30:31.246
I have a nice piece of 1095.

30:31.246 --> 30:34.249
I'll be able to get
to the point of grinding

30:34.249 --> 30:35.917
way faster now.

30:35.917 --> 30:37.711
<i>[cymbal shimmering]</i>

30:37.711 --> 30:39.296
<i>‐ So far,</i>
<i>everything's going smoothly.</i>

30:39.296 --> 30:41.173
What I wanna get done today is,

30:41.173 --> 30:43.425
<i>I wanna get my blade</i>
<i>heat‐treated.</i>

30:43.425 --> 30:45.135
<i>[rock music]</i>

30:45.135 --> 30:46.803
<i>The heat treat is a part</i>
<i>of making a knife</i>

30:46.803 --> 30:48.472
<i>I normally don't</i>
<i>struggle with.</i>

30:48.472 --> 30:50.599
However, I'm not used to

30:50.599 --> 30:53.143
quenching a blade this big.

30:53.143 --> 30:54.728
All right, here we go.

30:54.728 --> 30:57.397
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:57.397 --> 30:58.940
<i>I don't hear any tings</i>

30:58.940 --> 31:01.902
or any sounds of cracking.

31:01.902 --> 31:03.987
[mutters] Oh, my God.

31:03.987 --> 31:06.448
I got a little bit of a bend.

31:06.448 --> 31:07.949
<i>I can't fix these warps.</i>

31:07.949 --> 31:09.326
<i>I only have one option.</i>

31:09.326 --> 31:11.787
That's to go for
the quench again.

31:11.787 --> 31:14.372
<i>[tense music]</i>

31:14.372 --> 31:17.542
The same problem happens.

31:17.542 --> 31:19.211
I'm gonna try it one more time.

31:19.211 --> 31:20.712
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:20.712 --> 31:22.756
I think I'm just
compounding the problem

31:22.756 --> 31:26.176
<i>by introducing more and more</i>
<i>stresses into the blade.</i>

31:26.176 --> 31:27.761
If this doesn't work,

31:27.761 --> 31:29.930
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

31:29.930 --> 31:32.766
If the heat treat isn't right,
the blade just won't perform.

31:32.766 --> 31:34.518
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:37.437 --> 31:39.564
‐ Lord, I hope
third time's a charm.

31:39.564 --> 31:41.525
My blade is warped,

31:41.525 --> 31:43.985
<i>so I'm gonna try one more time</i>

31:43.985 --> 31:46.363
<i>to quench this blade.</i>

31:46.363 --> 31:48.073
It's a final Hail Mary.

31:48.073 --> 31:51.159
<i>[tense music]</i>

31:51.159 --> 31:53.912
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:53.912 --> 31:55.956
<i>[solemn music]</i>

31:55.956 --> 31:57.666
No.

31:57.666 --> 31:59.084
While the blade
is cooling down,

31:59.084 --> 32:00.418
<i>the warps keep coming.</i>

32:00.418 --> 32:02.295
<i>The best course of action</i>

32:02.295 --> 32:04.381
is just to forge out
a new blade.

32:04.381 --> 32:06.883
<i>[tense tone]</i>

32:06.883 --> 32:08.593
<i>‐ Start of day four,</i>

32:08.593 --> 32:11.096
<i>I'd like both the guard</i>
<i>and the pommel</i>

32:11.096 --> 32:13.014
forged to shape.

32:13.014 --> 32:15.725
This is the bane
of my existence.

32:15.725 --> 32:19.146
I really want a power hammer.

32:19.146 --> 32:21.481
Gonna jump right into
more grinding.

32:21.481 --> 32:23.233
<i>I still have a lot of material</i>
<i>on the sword</i>

32:23.233 --> 32:26.194
that I want to go away.

32:26.194 --> 32:27.571
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:27.571 --> 32:30.157
<i>My overall weight goal</i>
<i>is 3 1/2 pounds,</i>

32:30.157 --> 32:34.452
so I need to drop this thing
by essentially a pound.

32:34.452 --> 32:36.163
It's getting there;
it's taking shape.

32:36.163 --> 32:38.415
It's a little too heavy,

32:38.415 --> 32:40.417
but I think it will kill.

32:40.417 --> 32:41.918
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:41.918 --> 32:44.588
‐ Yesterday, I forged out
an entire new sword,

32:44.588 --> 32:48.300
<i>and after my heat treat,</i>
<i>I still had a warp in it.</i>

32:48.300 --> 32:50.594
I ended up deciding
to go back to my first sword,

32:50.594 --> 32:52.929
because now that I've been
grinding up bevels,

32:52.929 --> 32:56.141
<i>you can hardly tell</i>
<i>it was warped.</i>

32:56.141 --> 33:00.395
Today, I need to shape out
my Damascus guard

33:00.395 --> 33:02.564
and get it fitted on the tang.

33:02.564 --> 33:04.274
<i>I just drew</i>
<i>kind of a rough shape</i>

33:04.274 --> 33:05.692
<i>of how I want my guard to be.</i>

33:05.692 --> 33:08.528
I want it to be kind of a‐‐
have an upsweep,

33:08.528 --> 33:11.364
<i>with wings pointing forward.</i>

33:11.364 --> 33:13.825
I feel like I'm in
a pretty good place still,

33:13.825 --> 33:15.660
<i>even after losing</i>
<i>an entire day.</i>

33:15.660 --> 33:17.370
<i>Think I can still get</i>

33:17.370 --> 33:19.164
<i>a really good fit</i>
<i>and finish on my blade,</i>

33:19.164 --> 33:22.042
and make everything
just how I want.

33:23.668 --> 33:25.128
<i>[rock music]</i>

33:25.128 --> 33:26.463
<i>‐ Day five.</i>

33:26.463 --> 33:28.632
Woot. Let's go.

33:28.632 --> 33:30.884
<i>I essentially have</i>
<i>all of the fit and finish</i>

33:30.884 --> 33:33.220
<i>still left to do.</i>

33:33.220 --> 33:36.306
I still have the pommel
to thread;

33:36.306 --> 33:38.183
<i>I have the handle to form.</i>

33:38.183 --> 33:41.144
<i>The fit and finish is</i>
<i>my least favorite part.</i>

33:41.144 --> 33:43.813
<i>If I could have an apprentice</i>

33:43.813 --> 33:46.149
<i>who would do all that for me,</i>

33:46.149 --> 33:49.402
<i>that would be the best</i>
<i>arrangement in the world.</i>

33:49.402 --> 33:51.821
It takes a big guy
to swing a sword like this.

33:51.821 --> 33:55.659
<i>[solemn music]</i>

33:55.659 --> 33:58.870
‐ Michael, Ethan,
welcome back to The Forge.

33:58.870 --> 34:00.789
You've had five days
at your home forges

34:00.789 --> 34:03.250
to work on
your barbarian swords.

34:03.250 --> 34:05.460
Michael, how did it go for you?

34:05.460 --> 34:08.088
‐ I think reasonably well.

34:08.088 --> 34:10.006
<i>Forged the blade out of 1095,</i>

34:10.006 --> 34:13.009
<i>and a little layer of Damascus</i>
<i>for both the guard and pommel.</i>

34:13.009 --> 34:16.471
<i>Hickory wood handle core,</i>
<i>wrapped in leather.</i>

34:16.471 --> 34:18.598
‐ Ethan, how'd it go for you?

34:18.598 --> 34:21.142
‐ I forged the blade
out of 5160.

34:21.142 --> 34:22.852
<i>Did a Damascus guard,</i>

34:22.852 --> 34:25.647
<i>and the pommel was made</i>
<i>out of powdered steel</i>

34:25.647 --> 34:28.316
<i>and scrapped submarine</i>
<i>hole shavings.</i>

34:28.316 --> 34:30.443
<i>The wood core</i>
<i>is made of rosewood,</i>

34:30.443 --> 34:33.780
wrapped in natural colored
buckskin.

34:33.780 --> 34:35.991
‐ Gentlemen,
each of your blades

34:35.991 --> 34:39.160
will now be put through
a series of barbaric tests.

34:39.160 --> 34:41.871
There will be a strength test,
a sharpness test,

34:41.871 --> 34:43.999
and up first, the kill test.

34:43.999 --> 34:45.041
Doug?

34:45.041 --> 34:47.377
<i>[tense music]</i>

34:47.377 --> 34:48.795
‐ Bladesmiths, to find out

34:48.795 --> 34:50.964
what kinda lethal damage
your weapon will do,

34:50.964 --> 34:52.465
I will take
your barbarian sword

34:52.465 --> 34:56.261
and lovingly caress
the edge of the torso,

34:56.261 --> 34:59.723
pierce its soul with its tip.

34:59.723 --> 35:01.182
Basically the barbaric way.

35:01.182 --> 35:03.059
[both chuckle]
Michael, you're up first.

35:03.059 --> 35:04.936
You ready?
‐ Oh, yeah.

35:04.936 --> 35:06.688
‐ Let's do this.

35:06.688 --> 35:08.565
<i>‐ I'm nervous that my sword's</i>
<i>a little bit heavy,</i>

35:08.565 --> 35:14.195
<i>but it feels so cool</i>
<i>to see Doug wielding my sword.</i>

35:14.195 --> 35:16.573
[exhales]

35:16.573 --> 35:19.993
<i>[rock music]</i>

35:19.993 --> 35:21.703
Oh, my God.

35:21.703 --> 35:23.913
‐ [grunting]

35:23.913 --> 35:26.124
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:26.124 --> 35:28.710
‐ Jesus...

35:28.710 --> 35:30.587
‐ [grunts slowly]

35:30.587 --> 35:33.882
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:33.882 --> 35:36.926
[grunting]

35:36.926 --> 35:39.512
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:39.512 --> 35:41.431
<i>[cymbal shimmering]</i>

35:41.431 --> 35:44.559
<i>[solemn music]</i>

35:44.559 --> 35:48.521
‐ Mike, just the movement alone
and the balance of your blade

35:48.521 --> 35:51.316
allows for deep crushing cuts.

35:51.316 --> 35:53.276
Not only does it cut the skin,

35:53.276 --> 35:56.613
it goes into the bone and into
the organs right behind it.

35:56.613 --> 35:58.365
‐ Nice.
‐ Your weapon, sir...

35:58.365 --> 36:00.950
will definitely kill.

36:00.950 --> 36:03.244
Good job.
‐ Thank you.

36:03.244 --> 36:05.080
‐ All right, Ethan, you ready?

36:05.080 --> 36:07.457
‐ Let's do it.
‐ Let's do this.

36:07.457 --> 36:09.292
<i>‐ Getting to watch</i>
<i>Michael go first</i>

36:09.292 --> 36:12.962
is about as nerve‐racking for
me as watching my own blade.

36:12.962 --> 36:15.465
<i>He killed</i>
<i>that ballistic dummy.</i>

36:15.465 --> 36:17.801
<i>[music intensifies]</i>

36:17.801 --> 36:20.470
<i>[rock music]</i>

36:20.470 --> 36:23.139
<i>♪</i> ♪

36:23.139 --> 36:26.643
‐ [grunting]

36:26.643 --> 36:33.316
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:33.316 --> 36:34.943
[grunts]

36:34.943 --> 36:39.322
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:39.322 --> 36:41.324
[all chuckling]

36:41.324 --> 36:43.034
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:43.034 --> 36:45.995
‐ Now, Ethan, let's talk
about your barbarian sword.

36:45.995 --> 36:49.040
The balance and the weight,
it's unbelievable.

36:49.040 --> 36:51.167
It feels that you can
wield it continuously

36:51.167 --> 36:52.502
and move around.

36:52.502 --> 36:54.504
This is what you wanna
carry into battle.

36:54.504 --> 36:56.214
It's strong enough
and sharp enough

36:56.214 --> 36:58.091
to lacerate into the chest,

36:58.091 --> 37:01.928
break the bones,
and get into the organs.

37:01.928 --> 37:03.763
Because of that...

37:03.763 --> 37:05.849
it will kill.

37:05.849 --> 37:08.143
‐ Gentlemen,
welcome to the strength test.

37:08.143 --> 37:09.769
The answer to the riddle
in this steel

37:09.769 --> 37:12.230
lies in the correct
edge geometry and heat treat,

37:12.230 --> 37:13.773
and to test those things,

37:13.773 --> 37:15.400
as well as the overall
construction of your swords,

37:15.400 --> 37:17.902
I'm gonna be bashing away
on this battering ram.

37:17.902 --> 37:19.404
Remember, this test
is all about

37:19.404 --> 37:20.864
what the ram does
to your swords,

37:20.864 --> 37:23.366
and not what the swords
do to the ram.

37:23.366 --> 37:24.784
Michael, you're up first.
Are you ready?

37:24.784 --> 37:26.119
‐ Oh, yeah. Let's go.

37:26.119 --> 37:29.205
<i>[dynamic percussive music]</i>

37:29.205 --> 37:36.296
<i>♪</i> ♪

37:45.513 --> 37:47.307
[chuckles] Yes.

37:47.307 --> 37:48.892
‐ Nice.

37:48.892 --> 37:50.393
<i>[solemn music]</i>

37:50.393 --> 37:54.230
‐ Michael, this is
so much fun to swing.

37:54.230 --> 37:58.067
There's no edge deformation
that I can see at all.

37:58.067 --> 37:59.319
The handle is comfortable.

37:59.319 --> 38:00.904
The only thing
I could say at all

38:00.904 --> 38:03.239
is that the cross guard has
some sharp corners here,

38:03.239 --> 38:05.575
and they kinda bit into my
fingers as I was swinging it.

38:05.575 --> 38:09.162
But aside from that,
it's a wonderful sword.

38:09.162 --> 38:10.747
Well done.
‐ Thank you.

38:10.747 --> 38:13.166
‐ Ethan, are you ready?
‐ Let's do it.

38:13.166 --> 38:14.250
‐ Let's do it.

38:14.250 --> 38:16.753
<i>[tense music]</i>

38:16.753 --> 38:19.380
‐ [exhales]
Good luck.

38:19.380 --> 38:21.132
<i>♪</i> ♪

38:21.132 --> 38:24.427
<i>[rock music]</i>

38:24.427 --> 38:31.476
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:34.687 --> 38:37.273
‐ [mouths words]
‐ [chuckles]

38:37.273 --> 38:39.901
Wow.

38:39.901 --> 38:41.569
‐ This thing is amazing.

38:41.569 --> 38:44.531
It's light;
it's beautifully balanced.

38:44.531 --> 38:47.367
It was easy to control.
Took no damage.

38:47.367 --> 38:49.786
I love that I can choke
right up to the guard here,

38:49.786 --> 38:52.121
and it's just super comfortable
the whole time.

38:52.121 --> 38:53.706
Really well done.

38:53.706 --> 38:55.041
‐ Thank you.
‐ Nice, dude.

38:55.041 --> 38:58.795
<i>[solemn music]</i>

38:58.795 --> 39:00.964
‐ All right, gentlemen, it's
time for the sharpness test.

39:00.964 --> 39:02.465
Now, to test the sharpness
of your edge,

39:02.465 --> 39:04.592
I'll be slashing
and hacking into this hide.

39:04.592 --> 39:07.220
A sharp edge should give me
a good, clean cut.

39:07.220 --> 39:10.974
A dull edge: tear, rip,
it will just bounce right off.

39:10.974 --> 39:13.142
You ready?
‐ Let's go.

39:13.142 --> 39:14.936
‐ All right, Michael.

39:14.936 --> 39:16.229
<i>‐ During the kill test,</i>

39:16.229 --> 39:18.231
both our blades
performed awesome.

39:18.231 --> 39:21.484
<i>The strength test: neither</i>
<i>of our blades took damage.</i>

39:21.484 --> 39:23.611
So now, for the sharpness test,

39:23.611 --> 39:26.155
<i>one of our blades</i>
<i>needs to do better.</i>

39:26.155 --> 39:28.575
Oh, boy.
I really hope it's mine.

39:28.575 --> 39:30.159
<i>[music intensifies]</i>

39:34.998 --> 39:42.171
<i>♪</i> ♪

39:49.679 --> 39:52.807
<i>[solemn music]</i>

39:52.807 --> 39:54.225
All right, Michael,

39:54.225 --> 39:56.394
when I made that first punch
through the skin,

39:56.394 --> 39:58.062
I was expecting
some resistance,

39:58.062 --> 39:59.522
and there wasn't any.

39:59.522 --> 40:01.274
Your edge is beautiful.

40:01.274 --> 40:03.026
Your guard, I mean,
I kinda like

40:03.026 --> 40:05.528
<i>the way you've got that</i>
<i>sort of an S shape to it,</i>

40:05.528 --> 40:07.196
but it bites a little bit
on the hand.

40:07.196 --> 40:08.907
But, uh, this is a sword

40:08.907 --> 40:10.867
that you could just play with
all day long.

40:10.867 --> 40:12.243
Nicely done.

40:12.243 --> 40:13.786
All right, Ethan, you're up.
Are you ready?

40:13.786 --> 40:15.622
‐ Let's do it.
‐ Okay.

40:15.622 --> 40:18.708
‐ We are pretty much at a
dead heat in this competition.

40:18.708 --> 40:21.794
<i>I need to have my blade</i>
<i>cut that thing</i>

40:21.794 --> 40:24.130
as well or better than his did.

40:24.130 --> 40:25.757
<i>[music swells]</i>

40:25.757 --> 40:28.801
<i>[rock music]</i>

40:28.801 --> 40:35.350
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:39.228 --> 40:42.482
<i>[soft dynamic music]</i>

40:42.482 --> 40:44.609
‐ So, this sword,

40:44.609 --> 40:46.402
it's light, it's fast.

40:46.402 --> 40:49.364
The balance is right back here
in my hand.

40:49.364 --> 40:50.782
Nothing's pulling the tip.

40:50.782 --> 40:52.367
I know exactly where
the tip is.

40:52.367 --> 40:55.578
The cuts are beautiful;
sharp blade.

40:55.578 --> 40:57.538
A great cutter. Nicely done.

40:57.538 --> 40:59.123
‐ Thank you.

40:59.123 --> 41:03.419
‐ Michael, Ethan,
this was not an easy decision,

41:03.419 --> 41:05.380
but a decision has been made.

41:05.380 --> 41:08.091
The "Forged in Fire"
champion is...

41:08.091 --> 41:11.260
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

41:11.260 --> 41:13.721
Ethan. Good job.

41:13.721 --> 41:17.016
Michael, I don't wanna say
your blade didn't make the cut,

41:17.016 --> 41:18.851
because it definitely cuts,

41:18.851 --> 41:20.561
but in this particular case,

41:20.561 --> 41:22.855
you are not
the "Forged in Fire" champion.

41:22.855 --> 41:26.359
‐ Michael, you brought us
an amazing barbarian sword.

41:26.359 --> 41:28.528
You should be proud...
‐ [mouths words]

41:28.528 --> 41:30.738
‐ It came down to
the finer details:

41:30.738 --> 41:32.991
balance, comfort,
ounces of weight.

41:32.991 --> 41:34.242
Ethan won.

41:34.242 --> 41:36.285
You didn't lose.
‐ [mouths words]

41:36.285 --> 41:39.455
‐ Michael, the craftsmanship
on that blade is incredible.

41:39.455 --> 41:41.708
Please give it to me...
[laughter]

41:41.708 --> 41:43.167
Right now. Come on.

41:43.167 --> 41:44.794
<i>‐ I'm feeling disappointed,</i>

41:44.794 --> 41:47.046
<i>a little deflated,</i>

41:47.046 --> 41:49.257
but at the same time,
I‐‐[exhales]‐‐

41:49.257 --> 41:51.134
<i>I think I did well.</i>

41:51.134 --> 41:54.345
It's a tough competition,
and I'm really proud of myself.

41:54.345 --> 41:57.181
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:57.181 --> 41:58.933
‐ Ethan, congratulations.

41:58.933 --> 42:00.560
You are the "Forged in Fire"
champion,

42:00.560 --> 42:02.562
and that is a title
that comes with a check

42:02.562 --> 42:04.230
for $10,000.

42:04.230 --> 42:07.066
Please present your weapon
to the judges.

42:07.066 --> 42:09.110
‐ Wow, I don't know
what to say.

42:09.110 --> 42:10.820
<i>It's a very humbling feeling</i>

42:10.820 --> 42:13.156
<i>to know that I won</i>
<i>a competition</i>

42:13.156 --> 42:15.116
<i>against an awesome sword</i>

42:15.116 --> 42:17.410
<i>and excellent bladesmith.</i>

42:17.410 --> 42:19.328
<i>Never stop pursuing</i>
<i>your dreams,</i>

42:19.328 --> 42:20.913
<i>no matter how crazy they are,</i>

42:20.913 --> 42:23.708
because of all the dreams
I'm going after,

42:23.708 --> 42:25.001
this is just the beginning.

42:25.001 --> 42:30.006
<i>♪ ♪</i>
